wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the Gamasa Properties project overview section. Explain the platform's purpose as a vacation rental marketplace for Jemsea, Egypt, connecting property owners with tenants. Document the target audience, core value proposition, and key differentiators. Describe the business model, revenue streams, and market positioning. Include the technology stack overview, architectural approach, and scalability considerations. Provide context about the real estate rental industry in Egypt and how Gamasa Properties addresses market gaps. Use terminology consistent with the codebase and include practical examples of user workflows and business scenarios.

Explain the component organization strategy, reusable UI components, and responsive design patterns. Detail the internationalization setup with Arabic and English fonts, RTL layout handling, and mobile-first design approach. Detail Next.js bundle analyzer integration, webpack bundle visualization, and dependency size analysis. Document performance profiling tools, Lighthouse integration, and Core Web Vitals monitoring. Explain bundle optimization techniques, unused code elimination, and dependency tree analysis. Include examples of identifying performance bottlenecks, measuring optimization impact, and establishing performance budgets. Cover continuous performance monitoring, automated performance testing, and performance regression prevention strategies.

wiki_catalogs.name: Threat Mitigation and Monitoring
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop threat mitigation and monitoring documentation for Gamasa Properties. Detail security monitoring implementation, threat detection mechanisms, and incident response procedures. Explain rate limiting strategies, brute force attack prevention, and suspicious activity detection. Document security logging practices, anomaly detection, and automated security alerts. Include examples of implementing CAPTCHA systems, IP blocking mechanisms, and account lockout policies. Provide guidelines for security event logging, monitoring dashboard implementation, and establishing security incident response workflows.

wiki_catalogs.name: Property Management System
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create detailed property management system documentation for Gamasa Properties. Document the property data model, CRUD operations implementation, property listing and search functionality, and property categorization system. Explain property creation workflow, image upload and management, property validation rules, and approval processes. Detail the property filtering and sorting mechanisms, geolocation integration, and property availability management. Include property owner dashboard features, property modification workflows, and property deletion procedures. Provide examples of property data structures, API interactions, and UI component implementations.

Detail the notification system for verification status changes, owner communication channels, and appeal processes. wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Gamasa Properties - Real Estate Rental Platform

## Project Introduction

**Gamasa Properties** is a modern real estate rental platform specializing in vacation rentals and short-term accommodations in Jemsa, Egypt. The platform connects property owners with tenants seeking temporary housing for vacations, business trips, or extended stays.

### Purpose Statement
The platform aims to revolutionize the vacation rental market in Jemsa by providing an intuitive, mobile-first solution for property listings, secure booking systems, and seamless communication between owners and tenants.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Primary Goal**: Establish Jemsa as a premier vacation destination through innovative property rental technology
- **User Experience**: Deliver a seamless, Arabic-language experience optimized for mobile devices
- **Market Expansion**: Connect local property owners with international and domestic travelers
- **Trust Building**: Implement verification systems and secure payment processing

### Target Audience
- **Property Owners**: Local homeowners and real estate agents looking to rent out vacation properties
- **Tenants**: Tourists, business travelers, and locals seeking temporary accommodation
- **Administrators**: Platform moderators managing listings and user interactions

## Technical Architecture

The application follows a modern Next.js 16 architecture with a comprehensive TypeScript implementation and Supabase backend integration.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Client Application] --> B[Next.js App Router]
    B --> C[React Components]
    B --> D[Server Actions]
    C --> E[UI Components]
    C --> F[Context Providers]
    D --> G[Supabase Service Layer]
    G --> H[Supabase Backend]
    G --> I[Storage Service]
    H --> J[(PostgreSQL Database)]
    I --> K[(Cloud Storage)]
    
    subgraph "Authentication Flow"
        L[Auth Context] --> M[Local Storage]
        L --> N[Supabase Auth]
        M --> O[Mock Mode]
        N --> P[Real Auth]
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        Q[Type System] --> R[Database Types]
        R --> S[API Services]
        S --> T[Component Integration]
    end
```

### Component Breakdown

The architecture implements a layered approach with clear separation of concerns:

**Frontend Layer**
- **App Router**: Modern file-based routing with dynamic imports
- **Component Library**: Reusable UI components with Tailwind CSS styling
- **State Management**: Context-based authentication and global state
- **UI System**: Custom glass-morphism design with dark/light theme support

**Backend Layer**
- **Supabase Integration**: Real-time database, authentication, and storage
- **Service Layer**: Business logic encapsulation and data transformation
- **Storage Management**: Local storage fallback and cloud storage integration

**Data Layer**
- **Type System**: Comprehensive TypeScript interfaces for type safety
- **Database Schema**: Well-defined tables for properties, users, bookings, and communications
- **API Abstraction**: Unified service layer for database operations

### Design Patterns

The application implements several key design patterns:

- **Provider Pattern**: Centralized state management through React Context
- **Service Layer Pattern**: Business logic encapsulation in dedicated services
- **Factory Pattern**: Dynamic component creation and configuration
- **Observer Pattern**: Real-time updates through Supabase subscriptions
- **Repository Pattern**: Data access abstraction for database operations

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points

**Application Bootstrap**
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with metadata, fonts, and theme configuration
- `src/app/providers.tsx` - Provider wrapper for theme, auth, and toast contexts
- `src/context/AuthContext.tsx` - Central authentication state management

**Routing Structure**
- `src/app/page.tsx` - Home page with property listings and search functionality
- `src/app/property/[id]/page.tsx` - Property detail page with booking integration
- `src/app/auth/page.tsx` - Authentication forms and user registration

### Core Modules

**Authentication System**
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant AC as AuthContext
    participant LS as LocalStorage
    participant SB as Supabase
    
    U->>AC: Login Request
    AC->>LS: Check Local Storage
    alt Mock Mode Active
        LS-->>AC: Return Mock User
    else Real Auth Required
        AC->>SB: Authenticate User
        SB-->>AC: Return Auth Session
    end
    AC->>U: Provide Auth State
```

**Property Management Service**
The service layer handles all property-related operations with comprehensive CRUD functionality and mock mode support for development.

**Storage Management**
Dual-mode storage system supporting both local development (localStorage) and production (Supabase storage) environments.

### Configuration Approach

**Environment Configuration**
- `.env.local` - Local development environment variables
- `next.config.ts` - Next.js configuration with PWA support
- `tailwind.config.ts` - Styling configuration with custom color system
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript compilation settings

**Build System**
- Next.js 16 with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- PWA support for offline functionality

### External Dependencies

**Core Dependencies**
- `@supabase/supabase-js` - Real-time database and authentication
- `next` - React framework with App Router
- `react`, `react-dom` - Frontend framework
- `@supabase/ssr` - Server-side rendering support

**Development Dependencies**
- `typescript` - Type safety
- `tailwindcss` - Utility-first CSS framework
- `eslint` - Code quality and consistency

### Integration Points

**Third-Party Integrations**
- **Supabase**: Complete backend-as-a-service including database, auth, and storage
- **Google Fonts**: Arabic and Latin font support
- **Material Symbols**: Consistent iconography across the application
- **Leaflet Maps**: Interactive property location visualization

**API Endpoints**
- Property listing and management APIs
- User authentication and profile management
- Booking and payment processing
- Messaging and communication systems

### Component Relationship Diagrams

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[AuthContext] --> B[AuthProvider]
    A --> C[ProtectedRoute]
    B --> D[LocalStorage]
    B --> E[Supabase Auth]
    C --> F[Protected Components]
    F --> G[Navigation]
    F --> H[Content Areas]
    
    subgraph "UI Components"
        I[Header] --> J[Navigation]
        I --> K[Auth Buttons]
        L[PropertyCard] --> M[Favorite Toggle]
        L --> N[Image Display]
        O[Booking Form] --> P[Date Selection]
        O --> Q[Payment Methods]
    end
    
    subgraph "Service Layer"
        R[SupabaseService] --> S[Database Operations]
        R --> T[Storage Management]
        R --> U[Auth Management]
    end
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview

**Property Listing System**
- Comprehensive property search with filtering capabilities
- Detailed property cards with images, pricing, and features
- Location-based property discovery using interactive maps

**Booking and Payment System**
- Secure booking workflow with date selection
- Multiple payment method support (Vodafone Cash, Instapay, Fawry)
- Payment verification and property unlocking mechanisms

**User Management**
- Multi-role authentication (tenant, landlord, admin)
- Profile management and verification systems
- Favorites and saved searches functionality

**Communication Platform**
- Integrated messaging system between tenants and owners
- Real-time notifications and alerts
- WhatsApp integration for instant communication

### Implementation Highlights

**Real-time Updates**
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Loading
    Loading --> Authenticated: User Login
    Authenticated --> PropertyList: Load Properties
    PropertyList --> PropertyDetail: Select Property
    PropertyDetail --> BookingFlow: Initiate Booking
    BookingFlow --> PaymentProcessing: Submit Payment
    PaymentProcessing --> PropertyLocked: Payment Confirmed
    PropertyLocked --> BookingComplete: Owner Approval
    BookingComplete --> [*]
    
    PropertyList --> Favorites: Toggle Favorite
    Favorites --> PropertyList: Update List
```

**Responsive Design System**
- Mobile-first responsive layout
- Dark/light theme switching with system preference detection
- Touch-optimized navigation and interaction patterns

**Performance Optimization**
- Lazy loading for images and components
- Code splitting for improved initial load times
- Service worker integration for offline functionality

### Feature Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Interface] --> B[Component Layer]
    B --> C[Context Providers]
    C --> D[Service Layer]
    D --> E[Data Layer]
    
    subgraph "User Interface"
        F[Property Cards]
        G[Search Filters]
        H[Booking Forms]
        I[Messaging]
    end
    
    subgraph "Component Layer"
        J[Header Navigation]
        K[Property Details]
        L[Auth Forms]
        M[Admin Dashboard]
    end
    
    subgraph "Context Providers"
        N[Auth Context]
        O[Theme Provider]
        P[Toast Provider]
    end
    
    subgraph "Service Layer"
        Q[Supabase Service]
        R[Storage Service]
        S[Validation Service]
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        T[Local Storage]
        U[Supabase Database]
        V[Cloud Storage]
    end
```

The Gamasa Properties platform represents a comprehensive solution for the Egyptian vacation rental market, combining modern web technologies with local market understanding to create a seamless experience for both property owners and tenants in Jemsa.

**Sources:**
- [package.json](package.json)
- [layout.tsx](src/app/layout.tsx)
- [providers.tsx](src/app/providers.tsx)
- [AuthContext.tsx](src/context/AuthContext.tsx)
- [supabase.ts](src/lib/supabase.ts)
- [database.types.ts](src/types/database.types.ts)
- [page.tsx](src/app/page.tsx)
- [PropertyCard.tsx](src/components/PropertyCard.tsx)
- [supabaseService.ts](src/services/supabaseService.ts)
- [Header.tsx](src/components/Header.tsx)
- [storage.ts](src/lib/storage.ts)
- [next.config.ts](next.config.ts)
- [tailwind.config.ts](tailwind.config.ts)
- [property page.tsx](src/app/property/[id]/page.tsx)
- [client.tsx](src/app/property/[id]/client.tsx)

</blog>
